    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `SwizzleMode` enum to detect swizzle layout types (Quarter/32B, Half/64B, Full/128B)\n- Implement `DetectSwizzleMode` and `MergeSwizzleLayouts` functions in `gemm_layouts.cc`\n- When layout inference encounters conflicting swizzle layouts for the same buffer, automatically merge to the smaller granularity instead of raising an error\n- Refactor `GemmWGMMA.infer_shared_layout` to select swizzle layout based on continuity\n\n## Motivation\n\nWhen multiple operations (e.g., GEMM + Copy) require different swizzle layouts for the same shared memory buffer, the layout inference would fail with a conflict error. Since smaller swizzle granularity is compatible with larger ones (32B is compatible with 64B and 128B), we can automatically merge to the smaller granularity.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/layout/layout.h`: Add `SwizzleMode` enum and function declarations\n- `src/layout/gemm_layouts.cc`: Implement swizzle detection and merging logic\n- `src/transform/layout_inference.cc`: Add automatic swizzle layout merging in conflict resolution\n- `tilelang/tileop/gemm/gemm_wgmma.py`: Refactor shared layout inference with proper docstring\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Existing layout inference tests pass\n- [x] Flash attention backward pass with conflicting swizzle layouts now compiles successfully\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Accept additional float8 type aliases and allow specifying thread counts for correctness runs.\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Dynamic swizzle layout selection for GEMM to optimize shared-memory access.\n  * Smarter layout inference that attempts safe swizzle-aware merges before erroring.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Expanded multi-threaded correctness evaluation with parametrized thread values and guarded skipping for unsupported cases.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
